1) Define Product Vision
• 1.1.1 Finalize problem statement
→ Sellers see sales numbers but don’t know the reasons behind growth or decline
• 1.1.2 Define target users
→ Small & medium e-commerce sellers
→ D2C brands
→ Amazon / Flipkart sellers
→ Shopify store owners
• 1.1.3 Define value proposition
→ Provide AI-driven insights explaining sales trends
→ Detect reasons for drop/increase
→ Suggest actionable improvements
 Product Owner: Subani Mohammad
1.2 Create Product Backlog
• 1.2.1 List core features
• 1.2.2 Define MVP
• 1.2.3 Prioritize features (High / Medium / Low)
Example Backlog Items:
• Sales dashboard
• Upload sales data (CSV / API integration)
• Trend analysis (weekly / monthly)
• Sales drop detection
• AI-based “Reason Detection”
• Recommendation engine
• Competitor comparison
• Notification alerts
 Product Owner + Team
2) Sprint Planning Phase
2.1 Define Sprint Goal
Example Sprint Goal:
“Build a dashboard that shows sales trends and identifies major drops”
2.2 Create Sprint Backlog
Break backlog into technical tasks:
• 2.2.1 Setup database
• 2.2.2 Create API for sales data upload
• 2.2.3 Build trend analysis logic
• 2.2.4 Implement anomaly detection algorithm
• 2.2.5 Develop frontend dashboard UI
 Scrum Master :Humsika facilitates
